From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] bt: btpower: make bt_clk_enable idempotent

btpower has two independent "is BT powered" state trackers:

  - `pwr_state` in the ioctl handler (updated only when
    ioctl(BT_CMD_PWR_CTRL,...) flips the state),
  - `bt_chip_clk->is_enabled` (set by bt_clk_enable / cleared by
    bt_clk_disable),

and a THIRD power path that touches `is_enabled` without touching
`pwr_state`:

  - the rfkill callback `btpower_toggle_radio()` calls
    `bluetooth_power(!blocked)` directly,
  - userspace unblocks rfkill at boot, so by the time the QTI BT HAL
    opens /dev/btpower and calls `ioctl(BT_CMD_PWR_CTRL, 0)` then
    `ioctl(BT_CMD_PWR_CTRL, 1)`:
      * the (0) call is a no-op (pwr_state still 0, never updated
        by the rfkill path) -- no bt_clk_disable() runs,
      * the (1) call falls into bluetooth_power(1) -> bt_clk_enable()
        -> sees clk->is_enabled == 1 -> returns -EINVAL.

The HAL logs `ioctl failed to power control:-1 error =(Invalid
argument)`, ignores it, proceeds to open /dev/ttyHS0 and send the
HCI VS Get Version command, but the chip was never actually
re-asserted, so it never ACKs and the host-side bluebinder enters a
60s restart cascade.

bt_vreg_enable() is already idempotent on `vreg->is_enabled` (it
just skips its prepare/load/enable block); make bt_clk_enable() do
the same instead of returning -EINVAL on "already enabled". This
matches the regulator's behavior and makes the two parallel power
paths (ioctl + rfkill) safely interleave.

bt_clk_disable() keeps its existing strict check (it's only called
on the explicit power-off path; calling it on a not-enabled clock
is a real bug).

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [aurora bring-up bridge between ioctl
                                and rfkill power paths]

Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
---
 private/msm-google-modules/bt/pwr/btpower.c | 11 ++++++-----
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/private/msm-google-modules/bt/pwr/btpower.c b/private/msm-google-modules/bt/pwr/btpower.c
--- a/private/msm-google-modules/bt/pwr/btpower.c
+++ b/private/msm-google-modules/bt/pwr/btpower.c
@@ -397,11 +397,12 @@ static int bt_clk_enable(struct bt_power_clk_data *clk)

 	pr_info("%s: %s\n", __func__, clk->name);

-	/* Get the clock handle for vreg */
-	if (!clk->clk || clk->is_enabled) {
-		pr_err("%s: error - node: %p, clk->is_enabled:%d\n",
-			__func__, clk->clk, clk->is_enabled);
+	if (!clk->clk)
 		return -EINVAL;
+	if (clk->is_enabled) {
+		pr_info("%s: %s already enabled (idempotent)\n",
+			__func__, clk->name);
+		return 0;
 	}

 	rc = clk_prepare_enable(clk->clk);
